"{\"uid\": \"nbcsports.com-olympics-news-gymnastics-usa-championships-2024-men\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Brody Malone returned from three right leg surgeries in 2023 and went right back to the top of U.S. men's gymnastics as he bids for a second Olympics.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 150, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 5, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicholas_Brody\", \"score\": 0.9981780997331887, \"rank\": 0.001823330505772468, \"text\": \"Brody\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicholas_Brody\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicholas_Brody\"}, {\"begin\": 95, \"end\": 99, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9992249390288943, \"rank\": 0.0005953727125642021, \"text\": \"U.S.\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Malone, the 2021 and 2022 national champion, leads after the first of two nights of the Xfinity U.S. Championships.\", \"from\": 152, \"to\": 267, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 240, \"end\": 247, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NASCAR_Xfinity_Series\", \"score\": 0.880756906555812, \"rank\": 0.13173304154298243, \"text\": \"Xfinity\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NASCAR_Xfinity_Series\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NASCAR_Xfinity_Series\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In his first all-around competition in nearly 19 months, Malone had no major errors, stuck his closing high bar landing and tallied 85.95 points.\", \"from\": 269, \"to\": 414, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am usually the guy who does not show much emotion, but I kind of lost it there at the end,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 416, \"to\": 519, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"XFINITY U.S. CHAMPIONSHIPS:Results|Broadcast Schedule  He leads by 1.6 points over 2023 World bronze medalist Frederick Richard going into Saturday's final night of competition in Fort Worth, Texas.\", \"from\": 521, \"to\": 719, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 521, \"end\": 528, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NASCAR_Xfinity_Series\", \"score\": 0.880756906555812, \"rank\": 0.13173304154298243, \"text\": \"XFINITY\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NASCAR_Xfinity_Series\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NASCAR_Xfinity_Series\"}, {\"begin\": 631, \"end\": 640, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Frederick_the_Great\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.873493891727912e-14, \"text\": \"Frederick\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Frederick_the_Great\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Frederick_the_Great\"}, {\"begin\": 701, \"end\": 718, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Texas_Motor_Speedway\", \"score\": 0.9999999846538686, \"rank\": 1.5346063867196736e-08, \"text\": \"Fort Worth, Texas\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Texas_Motor_Speedway\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Texas_Motor_Speedway\"}, {\"begin\": 701, \"end\": 718, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Texas_Motor_Speedway\", \"score\": 0.9999999846538686, \"rank\": 1.5346063867196736e-08, \"text\": \"Fort Worth, Texas\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Texas_Motor_Speedway\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Texas_Motor_Speedway\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The five-man Paris Olympic team will be decided based largely on results this week and at the Olympic Trials from June 27-30 in Minneapolis.\", \"from\": 721, \"to\": 861, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 734, \"end\": 739, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999923504674, \"rank\": 7.649579040320268e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 849, \"end\": 860, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Minneapolis\", \"score\": 0.9999999999367901, \"rank\": 6.322962418860013e-11, \"text\": \"Minneapolis\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Minneapolis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Minneapolis\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At trials, the all-around winner makes the team if he is also among the top three on three of the six apparatus.\", \"from\": 863, \"to\": 975, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A committee picks the rest of the roster.\", \"from\": 976, \"to\": 1017, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"This was just one competition,\\\" said Malone, who competed with a mid-thigh-to-mid-calf brace on at least floor exercise and vault.\", \"from\": 1019, \"to\": 1150, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We still have another day to go, and then we have got two more (days of) trials.\", \"from\": 1151, \"to\": 1232, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So the work's not over yet.\\\"\", \"from\": 1233, \"to\": 1261, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"On March 18, 2023, Malone suffered a right tibial plateau fracture, meniscus tear, a partially torn PCL and a fully torn LCL in a high bar dismount fall.\", \"from\": 1263, \"to\": 1416, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1363, \"end\": 1366, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Posterior_cruciate_ligament\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.2842736386915836e-14, \"text\": \"PCL\", \"types\": [\"Q4936952\", \"Q39888\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Posterior_cruciate_ligament\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Posterior_cruciate_ligament\"}, {\"begin\": 1384, \"end\": 1387, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fibular_collateral_ligament\", \"score\": 0.9999999988190211, \"rank\": 1.1809969015425035e-09, \"text\": \"LCL\", \"types\": [\"Q4936952\", \"Q39888\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fibular_collateral_ligament\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fibular_collateral_ligament\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He underwent three surgeries, the last in June, was bedridden for a month and said heessentially relearned how to walk.\", \"from\": 1418, \"to\": 1537, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Malone, 24, returned to competition in January.\", \"from\": 1539, \"to\": 1586, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"On Thursday, he performed in the all-around (all six apparatus) for the first time since placing fourth at the 2022 World Championships.\", \"from\": 1587, \"to\": 1723, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Richard, who last year became the youngest U.S. man to win an individual world medal at 19, hit his foot on the pommel horse in his opening routine Thursday.\", \"from\": 1725, \"to\": 1882, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He climbed back, recording the second-best score on floor and high bar.\", \"from\": 1883, \"to\": 1954, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The endurance I had to handle not burning out at the end of the (competition), I could tell the hard work is paying off,\\\" said Richard, who competed collegiately for Michigan from January to April.\", \"from\": 1956, \"to\": 2154, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2123, \"end\": 2131, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michigan_Wolverines_men's_ice_hockey\", \"score\": 0.7746171364555228, \"rank\": 0.1456358288637421, \"text\": \"Michigan\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michigan_Wolverines_men's_ice_hockey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michigan_Wolverines_men's_ice_hockey\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Richard is followed in the all-around standings by Donnell Whittenburg and Colt Walker, who like Richard are trying to make their first Olympic team.\", \"from\": 2156, \"to\": 2305, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2207, \"end\": 2226, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donnell_Whittenburg\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Donnell Whittenburg\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donnell_Whittenburg\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donnell_Whittenburg\"}, {\"begin\": 2231, \"end\": 2242, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Colt_Walker\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.803304356616936e-18, \"text\": \"Colt Walker\", \"types\": [\"Q728\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Colt_Walker\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Colt_Walker\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Asher Hong, who last year at age 19 became the youngest U.S. men's all-around champion since 1989, is in 10th place.\", \"from\": 2307, \"to\": 2423, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2307, \"end\": 2317, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Asher_Hong\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Asher Hong\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Asher_Hong\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Asher_Hong\"}, {\"begin\": 2363, \"end\": 2367, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9992249390288943, \"rank\": 0.0005953727125642021, \"text\": \"U.S.\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He had significant errors on floor and pommel horse.\", \"from\": 2424, \"to\": 2476, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Nationals continue Friday with the first of two days of women's competition, live onPeacockfrom 8-10 p.m.\", \"from\": 2478, \"to\": 2583, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"ET.\", \"from\": 2584, \"to\": 2587, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A Division ofNBCUniversal.\", \"from\": 2591, \"to\": 2617, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2591, \"end\": 2601, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scottish_Football_League\", \"score\": 0.9999998398584594, \"rank\": 1.601415199112247e-07, \"text\": \"A Division\", \"types\": [\"Q623109\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scottish_Football_League\", \"dbpedia\": \"ht